The paper proposes a method for ontology alignment using external definition and context information, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and database systems (cs.DB) as it deals with merging ontologies and identifying semantically equivalent entities.
